  "text": "Both EF-Ts protein and cDNA were dramatically decreased in myocardium from the proband as compared with both FH and NFH, along with a reduction of EF-Tu protein. This last finding is in line with the likely destabilizing effect of the mutations on the EF-Ts/EF-Tu complex, as already reported [CITATION_1] . In contrast, protein and gene expression of EF-G1 were unchanged. A slight decrease of EF-Tu was also observed in FH versus NFH hearts (Fig. 5A,B and Supplementary Fig. S4 ).",
